	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Middle Persian</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Middle_Persian#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Middle_Persian#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="infobox vevent" style="width:22em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" class="above" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size:130%; color: black; background-color:  #c9ffd9;">Middle Persian</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:110%; color: black; background-color:  #c9ffd9;">ğ­¯ğ­ ğ­«ğ­®ğ­©ğ­ª (<i>PÄrsÄ«k</i> or <i>PÄrsÄ«g</i>)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;">Region</th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sasanian_Empire" title="Sasanian Empire">Sasanian Empire</a> (224â€“651)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;">Ethnicity</th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persians" title="Persians">Persian people</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;">Era</th><td style="line-height:1.3em;">Evolved into <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_language#New_Persian" title="Persian language">Early New Persian</a> by the 9th century; thereafter used only by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zoroastrianism" title="Zoroastrianism">Zoroastrian</a> priests for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exegesis" title="Exegesis">exegesis</a> and religious instruction</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><div style="padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;"><span class="wrap"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_family" title="Language family">Language family</a></span></div></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><div style="text-align:left;"><a href="Indo-European_languages" title="Indo-European languages">Indo-European</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:1.35em;padding-left:0"><li>
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indo-Iranian_languages" title="Indo-Iranian languages">Indo-Iranian</a><ul style="line-height:100%;margin-left:0.45em;padding-left:0;"><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iranian_languages" title="Iranian languages">Iranian</a><ul style="line-height:100%;margin-left:0.45em;padding-left:0;"><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Iranian_languages" title="Western Iranian languages">Western</a><ul style="line-height:100%;margin-left:0.45em;padding-left:0;"><li>Southwestern<ul style="line-height:100%;margin-left:0.45em;padding-left:0;"><li><b>Middle Persian</b></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><div style="padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Early form</div></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><div style="text-align:left;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Persian" title="Old Persian">Old Persian</a>
</div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><div style="padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;"><span class="wrap"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Writing_system" title="Writing system">Writing system</a></span></div></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pahlavi_scripts" title="Pahlavi scripts">Pahlavi scripts</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manichaean_alphabet" title="Manichaean alphabet">Manichaean alphabet</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avestan_alphabet" title="Avestan alphabet">Avestan alphabet</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;color: black; background-color:  #c9ffd9;">Language codes</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><span class="nowrap"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_639-2" title="ISO 639-2">ISO 639-2</a></span></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><code><span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.loc.gov/standards/iso639-2/php/langcodes_name.php?code_ID=350">pal</a></span></code></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><span class="nowrap"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_639-3" title="ISO 639-3">ISO 639-3</a></span></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;">Either:<br /><code><a href="https://iso639-3.sil.org/code/pal" class="extiw" title="iso639-3:pal">pal</a></code>&#160;â€“&#160;Zoroastrian Middle Persian ("Pahlavi")<br /><code><a href="https://iso639-3.sil.org/code/xmn" class="extiw" title="iso639-3:xmn">xmn</a></code>&#160;â€“&#160;Manichaean Middle Persian (Manichaean script)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glottolog" title="Glottolog">Glottolog</a></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><code><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://glottolog.org/resource/languoid/id/pahl1241">pahl1241</a></code>&#160; <span class="nowrap">Pahlavi</span><sup id="cite_ref-Glottolog_1-0" class="reference"><a href="Middle_Persian#cite_note-Glottolog-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguasphere_Observatory" title="Linguasphere Observatory">Linguasphere</a></th><td style="line-height:1.3em;"><code>58-AAC-ca</code></td></tr></tbody></table>
<table role="presentation" class="metadata mbox-small noprint selfref" style="background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000;width: 22em;">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/Farsi.svg/40px-Farsi.svg.png" decoding="async" width="40" height="29" srcset="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/Farsi.svg/60px-Farsi.svg.png 1.5x, http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/Farsi.svg/80px-Farsi.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="323" data-file-height="235" /></td>
<td class="mbox-text plainlist" style="vertical-align:middle; font-size:95%;"><b>This article contains <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_alphabet" title="Persian alphabet">Persian text</a>.</b> Without proper <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Arabic" title="Help:Arabic">rendering support</a>, you may see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Specials_(Unicode_block)#Replacement_character" title="Specials (Unicode block)">question marks, boxes, or other symbols</a>.</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<p><b>Middle Persian</b> or <b>Pahlavi</b>, also known by its <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endonym" class="mw-redirect" title="Endonym">endonym</a> <b>PÄrsÄ«k</b> or <b>PÄrsÄ«g</b> in its later form,<sup id="cite_ref-Mushegh_2-0" class="reference"><a href="Middle_Persian#cite_note-Mushegh-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="Middle_Persian#cite_note-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> is a Western <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iranian_languages#Middle_Iranian_languages" title="Iranian languages">Middle Iranian language</a> which became the literary language of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sasanian_Empire" title="Sasanian Empire">Sasanian Empire</a>. For some time after the Sasanian collapse, Middle Persian continued to function as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prestige_(sociolinguistics)" title="Prestige (sociolinguistics)">prestige language</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="Middle_Persian#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> It descended from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Persian" title="Old Persian">Old Persian</a>, the language of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Achaemenid_Empire" title="Achaemenid Empire">Achaemenid Empire</a> and is the linguistic ancestor of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_language#Modern_Persian" title="Persian language">Modern Persian</a>, the official language of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tajikistan" title="Tajikistan">Tajikistan</a>.
</p>
