<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Comparison_of_Middle_Persian_and_Modern_Persian_vocabulary">Comparison of Middle Persian and Modern Persian vocabulary</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Middle_Persian&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Comparison of Middle Persian and Modern Persian vocabulary">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>There are a number of phonological differences between Middle Persian and New Persian. The long vowels of Middle Persian did not survive in many present-day dialects. Also, initial <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consonant_cluster" title="Consonant cluster">consonant clusters</a> were very common in Middle Persian (e.g. <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%D8%B3%D9%BE%D8%A7%D8%B3" class="extiw" title="wikt:Ø³Ù¾Ø§Ø³">Ø³Ù¾Ø§Ø³</a> <b>sp</b>Äs "thanks"). However, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_language#New_Persian" title="Persian language">New Persian</a> does not allow initial consonant clusters, whereas final consonant clusters are common (e.g. <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%A8" class="extiw" title="wikt:Ø§Ø³Ø¨">Ø§Ø³Ø¨</a> a<b>sb</b> "horse").
</p>
